title: Rape victims in Scotland will be protected when giving evidence, says lord advocate
summary: The Supreme Court has ruled that 'rape shield' laws, which are designed to protect victims from intrusive cross-examination during trials, may potentially infringe on men's rights to a fair trial. This decision raises concerns about the balance between protecting victims and ensuring defendants receive due process. The ruling highlights the complexities of legal protections in sexual assault cases.
